cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular expressions and automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of the match test problem.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper mentions that the match test problem is NP-complete.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the combinatorial properties of extended regular expressions.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper uses the concept of pattern languages to specify extended regular expressions.
